title: 'Take it seriously': UN Security Council meets for first time about AI risks
description: The United Nations Security Council has been told to "take AI seriously" as it met for the first time to discuss the risks and opportunities of artificial intelligence.

title: Sailor rescued with dog after months lost at sea 'didn't think he would make it'
description: An Australian sailor who was rescued after being lost at sea for three months with his dog has said he is "grateful" to be alive.

title: What I learned when up against a 50C 'silent killer'
description: I'm wired up and covered in sensors. Guinea pig 16 in a study of how heat impacts the human body.

title: I felt at risk every hour of every day in Myanmar - but it was a risk worth taking
description: "What if nothing much is going on when you get there, and you're stuck for weeks?" one of the Sky News bosses asked.

title: Gigi Hadid arrested after cannabis found in luggage on holiday to Cayman Islands
description: Model Gigi Hadid was arrested last week in the Cayman Islands after being found with cannabis.

title: Dirty Work: The Misuse of Interpol Red Notices
description: Sahar Zand presents Dirty Work - a podcast series from Sky News about what happens when Red Notices go wrong.

title: Dinosaur and mammal discovered 'locked in mortal combat' from 125 million years ago
description: A plant-eating dinosaur and a mammal the size of a badger have been found "locked in mortal combat" from 125 million years ago.

title: Donald Trump 'notified he is target' of investigation into bids to overturn 2020 election
description: Donald Trump has said he has received a letter notifying him he is a target in a US Justice Department investigation into efforts to undo the results of the 2020 presidential election.

title: Workers pouring with sweat in blistering heatwave - but they have little choice
description: At the Mancini vineyard in the hills outside Olbia on the Italian island of Sardinia, Alessandro Mancini shows us the vines.

title: US state troopers 'told to push migrants back into river and deny them water'
description: Border security agents in Texas have allegedly been ordered to push migrants back into the Rio Grande river and to withhold water.

title: Soldier being held in North Korea was 'facing disciplinary action by US military'
description: An American soldier who is believed to be in custody in North Korea was facing disciplinary action by the US military when he crossed into the secretive country, US officials said.

title: US national 'crosses into North Korea from South Korea'
description: A US national has crossed the border from South Korea into North Korea, the UN Command in the region has said.

title: Watchmaker sues Malaysian government for seizing rainbow Pride watches
description: Swiss watchmaker Swatch is suing the Malaysian government for confiscating rainbow-coloured watches that celebrate LGBTQ rights.

title: Death toll in Kenya cult investigation passes 400 after members 'starved to meet Jesus'
description: Police investigating a Kenyan cult suspected of practising starvation to "meet Jesus" have exhumed over 400 bodies, a senior official has said.

title: Five killed after plane crashes into hangar where people were sheltering during bad weather
description: Five people have been killed and eight injured after a plane crashed into a hangar where people were sheltering during stormy weather in Poland.

title: Olympian named among crew for Virgin Galactic's first space tourism flight
description: A former Olympian has been named among the crew for Virgin Galactic's first space tourism flight.

title: Australian state pulls out of hosting 2026 Commonwealth Games
description: Australia's Victoria state has withdrawn as host of the 2026 Commonwealth Games because of a massive increase in the projected cost of staging the event.
